# pta syntax demo - converted from tests/demo.ledger
#
# pta vs ledger differences demonstrated here:
#   - amount comes BEFORE account   (ledger: account before amount)
#   - account names are lowercase   (pta default account regex)
#   - dates use ISO dashes          (ledger allows slashes)
#   - every posting has an amount   (ledger allows one elided/auto-balanced)
#   - payee on the header line is inherited as a tag by every posting
#   - a posting with its own date is a flat line: DATE amount account tags
#   - status flags (* !) and $ symbol are dropped (single-currency mode)
#
# Run:  cat tests/demo.pta | ./postings | ./balance

2010-12-01 Checking balance *
 1000 assets:checking
-1000 equity:opening_balances

# deferred grocery recognition: each posting carries its own effective date
# (flat format), while the checking withdrawal stays on the transaction date
2010-12-20 Organic Co-op
-225 assets:checking
2011-01-01 37.50 expenses:food:groceries
2011-02-01 37.50 expenses:food:groceries
2011-03-01 37.50 expenses:food:groceries
2011-04-01 37.50 expenses:food:groceries
2011-05-01 37.50 expenses:food:groceries
2011-06-01 37.50 expenses:food:groceries

2010-12-28 Acme Mortgage
 200 liabilities:mortgage:principal
 500 expenses:interest:mortgage
 300 expenses:escrow
-1000 assets:checking *

2011-01-02 Grocery Store
 65 expenses:food:groceries
-65 assets:checking

2011-01-05 Employer
 2000 assets:checking
-2000 income:salary

# payee plus a note -> both become tags on the postings
2011-01-14 Bank Regular monthly savings transfer
 300 assets:savings
-300 assets:checking :nobudget:

2011-01-19 Grocery Store
 44 expenses:food:groceries hastag:notblock
-44 assets:checking

2011-01-25 Bank Transfer to cover car purchase
 5500 assets:checking
-5500 assets:savings

2011-01-25 Tom's Used Cars
 5500 expenses:auto
-5500 assets:checking :nobudget:

2011-01-27 Book Store
 20 expenses:books
-20 liabilities:mastercard

2011-04-25 Tom's Used Cars
 5500 expenses:auto
-5500 assets:checking :nobudget:

2011-04-27 Bookstore
 20 expenses:books
-20 assets:checking

